## Summary

**Accomplished:** Fixed OCI runtime spec non-conformance bug (youki-2994) in the youki runtime.

**Root Cause:** In `crates/libcontainer/src/container/builder_impl.rs`, `createRuntime` hooks were executed **before** the container process was forked – i.e., before cgroups, device restrictions, namespaces, and mounts were set up. This violated the OCI spec, which requires these hooks to run **after** the container is created (with all resource constraints applied) but before the user process starts.

**Fix:** Moved the `createRuntime` hook execution block from before `container_main_process()` to immediately after it returns (but before setting the container status to `Created`). This ensures device cgroup restrictions and other container resources are in effect when hooks run.

